 {"id":"frankenpandas-ev2s","title":"fd90.18: SqlWriteOptions::dtype for per-column SQL-type overrides on CREATE TABLE","description":"fd90 sub-bead: per-column SQL-type override on writes. pandas to_sql(.., dtype={'col': SQLAlchemy_type}) lets users override the inferred SQL column type during CREATE TABLE. Add SqlWriteOptions::dtype: Option<BTreeMap<String, String>> with the value being the literal SQL type string (e.g. 'NUMERIC(10,2)' on PostgreSQL, 'DECIMAL(10,2)' on MySQL). Map entries for columns not in the frame are silently ignored (matches pandas). Override applies during CREATE TABLE column-def construction; falls back to conn.dtype_sql(DType) when no override. 4 tests covering single-column override, multiple overrides, missing-column ignored, no-override fallback.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:58:29.688908919Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:03:51.381676101Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:03:51.379195635Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dtype","fd90","review","sql"]}
